40/* Print an error message stemming from an attempt to use
41 BASETYPE as a base class for TYPE. */
42
43tree
44error_not_base_type (tree basetype, tree type)
45{
46 if (TREE_CODE (basetype) == FUNCTION_DECL)
47 basetype = DECL_CONTEXT (basetype);
48 error ("type %qT is not a base type for type %qT", basetype, type);
49 return error_mark_node;
50}
51
52tree
53binfo_or_else (tree base, tree type)
54{
55 tree binfo = lookup_base (type, base, ba_unique,
56 NULL, tf_warning_or_error);
57
58 if (binfo == error_mark_node)
59 return NULL_TREE;
60 else if (!binfo)
61 error_not_base_type (base, type);
62 return binfo;
63}

65/* According to ARM $7.1.6, "A `const' object may be initialized, but its
66 value may not be changed thereafter. */
67
68void
69cxx_readonly_error (tree arg, enum lvalue_use errstring)
70{
71
72/* This macro is used to emit diagnostics to ensure that all format
73 strings are complete sentences, visible to gettext and checked at
74 compile time. */
75
76#define ERROR_FOR_ASSIGNMENT(AS, ASM, IN, DE, ARG) \
77 do { \
78 switch (errstring) \
79 { \
80 case lv_assign: \
81 error(AS, ARG); \
82 break; \
83 case lv_asm: \
84 error(ASM, ARG); \
85 break; \
86 case lv_increment: \
87 error (IN, ARG); \
88 break; \
89 case lv_decrement: \
90 error (DE, ARG); \
91 break; \
92 default: \
93 gcc_unreachable (); \
94 } \
95 } while (0)
96
97 /* Handle C++-specific things first. */
98
99 if (VAR_P (arg)
100 && DECL_LANG_SPECIFIC (arg)
101 && DECL_IN_AGGR_P (arg)
102 && !TREE_STATIC (arg))
103 ERROR_FOR_ASSIGNMENT (G_("assignment of "
104 "constant field %qD"),
105 G_("constant field %qD "
106 "used as %<asm%> output"),
107 G_("increment of "
108 "constant field %qD"),
109 G_("decrement of "
110 "constant field %qD"),
111 arg);
112 else if (INDIRECT_REF_P (arg)
113 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0))) == REFERENCE_TYPE
114 && (VAR_P (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0))
115 || TREE_CODE (TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0)) == PARM_DECL))
116 ERROR_FOR_ASSIGNMENT (G_("assignment of "
117 "read-only reference %qD"),
118 G_("read-only reference %qD "
119 "used as %<asm%> output"),
120 G_("increment of "
121 "read-only reference %qD"),
122 G_("decrement of "
123 "read-only reference %qD"),
124 TREE_OPERAND (arg, 0));
125 else
126 readonly_error (input_location, arg, errstring);
127}

130/* Structure that holds information about declarations whose type was
131 incomplete and we could not check whether it was abstract or not. */
132
133struct GTY((chain_next ("%h.next"), for_user)) pending_abstract_type {
134 /* Declaration which we are checking for abstractness. It is either
135 a DECL node, or an IDENTIFIER_NODE if we do not have a full
136 declaration available. */
137 tree decl;
138
139 /* Type which will be checked for abstractness. */
140 tree type;
141
142 /* Kind of use in an unnamed declarator. */
143 enum abstract_class_use use;
144
145 /* Position of the declaration. This is only needed for IDENTIFIER_NODEs,
146 because DECLs already carry locus information. */
147 location_t locus;
148
149 /* Link to the next element in list. */
150 struct pending_abstract_type* next;
151};
152
153struct abstract_type_hasher : ggc_ptr_hash<pending_abstract_type>
154{
155 typedef tree compare_type;
156 static hashval_t hash (pending_abstract_type *);
157 static bool equal (pending_abstract_type *, tree);
158};
159
160/* Compute the hash value of the node VAL. This function is used by the
161 hash table abstract_pending_vars. */
162
163hashval_t
164abstract_type_hasher::hash (pending_abstract_type *pat)
165{
166 return (hashval_t) TYPE_UID (pat->type);
167}
168
169
170/* Compare node VAL1 with the type VAL2. This function is used by the
171 hash table abstract_pending_vars. */
172
173bool
174abstract_type_hasher::equal (pending_abstract_type *pat1, tree type2)
175{
176 return (pat1->type == type2);
177}
178
179/* Hash table that maintains pending_abstract_type nodes, for which we still
180 need to check for type abstractness. The key of the table is the type
181 of the declaration. */
182static GTY (()) hash_table<abstract_type_hasher> *abstract_pending_vars = NULL;
183
184static int abstract_virtuals_error_sfinae (tree, tree, abstract_class_use, tsubst_flags_t);
185
186/* This function is called after TYPE is completed, and will check if there
187 are pending declarations for which we still need to verify the abstractness
188 of TYPE, and emit a diagnostic (through abstract_virtuals_error) if TYPE
189 turned out to be incomplete. */
190
191void
192complete_type_check_abstract (tree type)
193{
194 struct pending_abstract_type *pat;
195 location_t cur_loc = input_location;
196
197 gcc_assert (COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type));
198
199 if (!abstract_pending_vars)
200 return;
201
202 /* Retrieve the list of pending declarations for this type. */
203 pending_abstract_type **slot
204 = abstract_pending_vars->find_slot_with_hash (type, TYPE_UID (type),
205 NO_INSERT);
206 if (!slot)
207 return;
208 pat = *slot;
209 gcc_assert (pat);
210
211 /* If the type is not abstract, do not do anything. */
212 if (CLASSTYPE_PURE_VIRTUALS (type))
213 {
214 struct pending_abstract_type *prev = 0, *next;
215
216 /* Reverse the list to emit the errors in top-down order. */
217 for (; pat; pat = next)
218 {
219 next = pat->next;
220 pat->next = prev;
221 prev = pat;
222 }
223 pat = prev;
224
225 /* Go through the list, and call abstract_virtuals_error for each
226 element: it will issue a diagnostic if the type is abstract. */
227 while (pat)
228 {
229 gcc_assert (type == pat->type);
230
231 /* Tweak input_location so that the diagnostic appears at the correct
232 location. Notice that this is only needed if the decl is an
233 IDENTIFIER_NODE. */
234 input_location = pat->locus;
235 abstract_virtuals_error_sfinae (pat->decl, pat->type, pat->use,
236 tf_warning_or_error);
237 pat = pat->next;
238 }
239 }
240
241 abstract_pending_vars->clear_slot (slot);
242
243 input_location = cur_loc;
244}

247/* If TYPE has abstract virtual functions, issue an error about trying
248 to create an object of that type. DECL is the object declared, or
249 NULL_TREE if the declaration is unavailable, in which case USE specifies
250 the kind of invalid use. Returns 1 if an error occurred; zero if
251 all was well. */
252
253static int
254abstract_virtuals_error_sfinae (tree decl, tree type, abstract_class_use use,
255 tsubst_flags_t complain)
256{
257 vec<tree, va_gc> *pure;
258
259 /* This function applies only to classes. Any other entity can never
260 be abstract. */
261 if (!CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
262 return 0;
263 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
264
265#if 0
266 /* Instantiation here seems to be required by the standard,
267 but breaks e.g. boost::bind. FIXME! */
268 /* In SFINAE, non-N3276 context, force instantiation. */
269 if (!(complain & (tf_error|tf_decltype)))
270 complete_type (type);
271#endif
272
273 /* If the type is incomplete, we register it within a hash table,
274 so that we can check again once it is completed. This makes sense
275 only for objects for which we have a declaration or at least a
276 name. */
277 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type) && (complain & tf_error))
278 {
279 struct pending_abstract_type *pat;
280
281 gcc_assert (!decl || DECL_P (decl) || identifier_p (decl));
282
283 if (!abstract_pending_vars)
284 abstract_pending_vars
285 = hash_table<abstract_type_hasher>::create_ggc (31);
286
287 pending_abstract_type **slot
288 = abstract_pending_vars->find_slot_with_hash (type, TYPE_UID (type),
289 INSERT);
290
291 pat = ggc_alloc<pending_abstract_type> ();
292 pat->type = type;
293 pat->decl = decl;
294 pat->use = use;
295 pat->locus = ((decl && DECL_P (decl))
296 ? DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (decl)
297 : input_location);
298
299 pat->next = *slot;
300 *slot = pat;
301
302 return 0;
303 }
304
305 if (!TYPE_SIZE (type))
306 /* TYPE is being defined, and during that time
307 CLASSTYPE_PURE_VIRTUALS holds the inline friends. */
308 return 0;
309
310 pure = CLASSTYPE_PURE_VIRTUALS (type);
311 if (!pure)
312 return 0;
313
314 if (!(complain & tf_error))
315 return 1;
316
317 if (decl)
318 {
319 if (VAR_P (decl))
320 error ("cannot declare variable %q+D to be of abstract "
321 "type %qT", decl, type);
322 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == PARM_DECL)
323 {
324 if (DECL_NAME (decl))
325 error ("cannot declare parameter %q+D to be of abstract type %qT",
326 decl, type);
327 else
328 error ("cannot declare parameter to be of abstract type %qT",
329 type);
330 }
331 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FIELD_DECL)
332 error ("cannot declare field %q+D to be of abstract type %qT",
333 decl, type);
334 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL
335 && TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (decl)) == METHOD_TYPE)
336 error ("invalid abstract return type for member function %q+#D", decl);
337 else if (TREE_CODE (decl) == FUNCTION_DECL)
338 error ("invalid abstract return type for function %q+#D", decl);
339 else if (identifier_p (decl))
340 /* Here we do not have location information. */
341 error ("invalid abstract type %qT for %qE", type, decl);
342 else
343 error ("invalid abstract type for %q+D", decl);
344 }
345 else switch (use)
346 {
347 case ACU_ARRAY:
348 error ("creating array of %qT, which is an abstract class type", type);
349 break;
350 case ACU_CAST:
351 error ("invalid cast to abstract class type %qT", type);
352 break;
353 case ACU_NEW:
354 error ("invalid new-expression of abstract class type %qT", type);
355 break;
356 case ACU_RETURN:
357 error ("invalid abstract return type %qT", type);
358 break;
359 case ACU_PARM:
360 error ("invalid abstract parameter type %qT", type);
361 break;
362 case ACU_THROW:
363 error ("expression of abstract class type %qT cannot "
364 "be used in throw-expression", type);
365 break;
366 case ACU_CATCH:
367 error ("cannot declare catch parameter to be of abstract "
368 "class type %qT", type);
369 break;
370 default:
371 error ("cannot allocate an object of abstract type %qT", type);
372 }
373
374 /* Only go through this once. */
375 if (pure->length ())
376 {
377 unsigned ix;
378 tree fn;
379
380 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (type)),
381 " because the following virtual functions are pure within %qT:",
382 type);
383
384 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (*pure, ix, fn)
385 if (! DECL_CLONED_FUNCTION_P (fn)
386 || DECL_COMPLETE_DESTRUCTOR_P (fn))
387 inform (DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn), "\t%#D", fn);
388
389 /* Now truncate the vector. This leaves it non-null, so we know
390 there are pure virtuals, but empty so we don't list them out
391 again. */
392 pure->truncate (0);
393 }
394
395 return 1;
396}

426/* Print an inform about the declaration of the incomplete type TYPE. */
427
428void
429cxx_incomplete_type_inform (const_tree type)
430{
431 if (!TYPE_MAIN_DECL (type))
432 return;
433
434 location_t loc = DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (TYPE_MAIN_DECL (type));
435 tree ptype = strip_top_quals (CONST_CAST_TREE (type));
436
437 if (current_class_type
438 && TYPE_BEING_DEFINED (current_class_type)
439 && same_type_p (ptype, current_class_type))
440 inform (loc, "definition of %q#T is not complete until "
441 "the closing brace", ptype);
442 else if (!TYPE_TEMPLATE_INFO (ptype))
443 inform (loc, "forward declaration of %q#T", ptype);
444 else
445 inform (loc, "declaration of %q#T", ptype);
446}

448/* Print an error message for invalid use of an incomplete type.
449 VALUE is the expression that was used (or 0 if that isn't known)
450 and TYPE is the type that was invalid. DIAG_KIND indicates the
451 type of diagnostic (see diagnostic.def). */
452
453void
454cxx_incomplete_type_diagnostic (location_t loc, const_tree value,
455 const_tree type, diagnostic_t diag_kind)
456{
457 bool is_decl = false, complained = false;
458
459 gcc_assert (diag_kind == DK_WARNING
460 || diag_kind == DK_PEDWARN
461 || diag_kind == DK_ERROR);
462
463 /* Avoid duplicate error message. */
464 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ERROR_MARK)
465 return;
466
467 if (value != 0 && (VAR_P (value)
468 || TREE_CODE (value) == PARM_DECL
469 || TREE_CODE (value) == FIELD_DECL))
470 {
471 complained = emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (value), 0,
472 "%qD has incomplete type", value);
473 is_decl = true;
474 }
475 retry:
476 /* We must print an error message. Be clever about what it says. */
477
478 switch (TREE_CODE (type))
479 {
480 case RECORD_TYPE:
481 case UNION_TYPE:
482 case ENUMERAL_TYPE:
483 if (!is_decl)
484 complained = emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
485 "invalid use of incomplete type %q#T",
486 type);
487 if (complained)
488 cxx_incomplete_type_inform (type);
489 break;
490
491 case VOID_TYPE:
492 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
493 "invalid use of %qT", type);
494 break;
495
496 case ARRAY_TYPE:
497 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
498 {
499 type = TREE_TYPE (type);
500 goto retry;
501 }
502 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
503 "invalid use of array with unspecified bounds");
504 break;
505
506 case OFFSET_TYPE:
507 bad_member:
508 {
509 tree member = TREE_OPERAND (value, 1);
510 if (is_overloaded_fn (member))
511 member = get_first_fn (member);
512 if (DECL_FUNCTION_MEMBER_P (member)
513 && ! flag_ms_extensions)
514 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
515 "invalid use of member function %qD "
516 "(did you forget the %<()%> ?)", member);
517 else
518 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
519 "invalid use of member %qD "
520 "(did you forget the %<&%> ?)", member);
521 }
522 break;
523
524 case TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM:
525 if (is_auto (type))
526 {
527 if (CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (type))
528 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
529 "invalid use of placeholder %qT", type);
530 else
531 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
532 "invalid use of %qT", type);
533 }
534 else
535 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
536 "invalid use of template type parameter %qT", type);
537 break;
538
539 case BOUND_TEMPLATE_TEMPLATE_PARM:
540 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
541 "invalid use of template template parameter %qT",
542 TYPE_NAME (type));
543 break;
544
545 case TYPENAME_TYPE:
546 case DECLTYPE_TYPE:
547 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
548 "invalid use of dependent type %qT", type);
549 break;
550
551 case LANG_TYPE:
552 if (type == init_list_type_node)
553 {
554 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
555 "invalid use of brace-enclosed initializer list");
556 break;
557 }
558 gcc_assert (type == unknown_type_node);
559 if (value && TREE_CODE (value) == COMPONENT_REF)
560 goto bad_member;
561 else if (value && TREE_CODE (value) == ADDR_EXPR)
562 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
563 "address of overloaded function with no contextual "
564 "type information");
565 else if (value && TREE_CODE (value) == OVERLOAD)
566 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
567 "overloaded function with no contextual type information");
568 else
569 emit_diagnostic (diag_kind, loc, 0,
570 "insufficient contextual information to determine type");
571 break;
572
573 default:
574 gcc_unreachable ();
575 }
576}

589/* The recursive part of split_nonconstant_init. DEST is an lvalue
590 expression to which INIT should be assigned. INIT is a CONSTRUCTOR.
591 Return true if the whole of the value was initialized by the
592 generated statements. */
593
594static bool
595split_nonconstant_init_1 (tree dest, tree init)
596{
597 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT idx;
598 tree field_index, value;
599 tree type = TREE_TYPE (dest);
600 tree inner_type = NULL;
601 bool array_type_p = false;
602 bool complete_p = true;
603 HOST_WIDE_INT num_split_elts = 0;
604
605 switch (TREE_CODE (type))
606 {
607 case ARRAY_TYPE:
608 inner_type = TREE_TYPE (type);
609 array_type_p = true;
610 if ((TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (init)
611 && TYPE_HAS_NONTRIVIAL_DESTRUCTOR (type))
612 || array_of_runtime_bound_p (type))
613 {
614 /* For an array, we only need/want a single cleanup region rather
615 than one per element. */
616 tree code = build_vec_init (dest, NULL_TREE, init, false, 1,
617 tf_warning_or_error);
618 add_stmt (code);
619 return true;
620 }
621 /* FALLTHRU */
622
623 case RECORD_TYPE:
624 case UNION_TYPE:
625 case QUAL_UNION_TYPE:
626 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init), idx,
627 field_index, value)
628 {
629 /* The current implementation of this algorithm assumes that
630 the field was set for all the elements. This is usually done
631 by process_init_constructor. */
632 gcc_assert (field_index);
633
634 if (!array_type_p)
635 inner_type = TREE_TYPE (field_index);
636
637 if (TREE_CODE (value) == CONSTRUCTOR)
638 {
639 tree sub;
640
641 if (array_type_p)
642 sub = build4 (ARRAY_REF, inner_type, dest, field_index,
643 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
644 else
645 sub = build3 (COMPONENT_REF, inner_type, dest, field_index,
646 NULL_TREE);
647
648 if (!split_nonconstant_init_1 (sub, value))
649 complete_p = false;
650 else
651 CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init)->ordered_remove (idx--);
652 num_split_elts++;
653 }
654 else if (!initializer_constant_valid_p (value, inner_type))
655 {
656 tree code;
657 tree sub;
658
659 /* FIXME: Ordered removal is O(1) so the whole function is
660 worst-case quadratic. This could be fixed using an aside
661 bitmap to record which elements must be removed and remove
662 them all at the same time. Or by merging
663 split_non_constant_init into process_init_constructor_array,
664 that is separating constants from non-constants while building
665 the vector. */
666 CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init)->ordered_remove (idx);
667 --idx;
668
669 if (TREE_CODE (field_index) == RANGE_EXPR)
670 {
671 /* Use build_vec_init to initialize a range. */
672 tree low = TREE_OPERAND (field_index, 0);
673 tree hi = TREE_OPERAND (field_index, 1);
674 sub = build4 (ARRAY_REF, inner_type, dest, low,
675 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
676 sub = cp_build_addr_expr (sub, tf_warning_or_error);
677 tree max = size_binop (MINUS_EXPR, hi, low);
678 code = build_vec_init (sub, max, value, false, 0,
679 tf_warning_or_error);
680 add_stmt (code);
681 if (tree_fits_shwi_p (max))
682 num_split_elts += tree_to_shwi (max);
683 }
684 else
685 {
686 if (array_type_p)
687 sub = build4 (ARRAY_REF, inner_type, dest, field_index,
688 NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE);
689 else
690 sub = build3 (COMPONENT_REF, inner_type, dest, field_index,
691 NULL_TREE);
692
693 code = build2 (INIT_EXPR, inner_type, sub, value);
694 code = build_stmt (input_location, EXPR_STMT, code);
695 code = maybe_cleanup_point_expr_void (code);
696 add_stmt (code);
697 if (tree cleanup
698 = cxx_maybe_build_cleanup (sub, tf_warning_or_error))
699 finish_eh_cleanup (cleanup);
700 }
701
702 num_split_elts++;
703 }
704 }
705 break;
706
707 case VECTOR_TYPE:
708 if (!initializer_constant_valid_p (init, type))
709 {
710 tree code;
711 tree cons = copy_node (init);
712 CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init) = NULL;
713 code = build2 (MODIFY_EXPR, type, dest, cons);
714 code = build_stmt (input_location, EXPR_STMT, code);
715 add_stmt (code);
716 num_split_elts += CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init);
717 }
718 break;
719
720 default:
721 gcc_unreachable ();
722 }
723
724 /* The rest of the initializer is now a constant. */
725 TREE_CONSTANT (init) = 1;
726 return complete_p && complete_ctor_at_level_p (TREE_TYPE (init),
727 num_split_elts, inner_type);
728}

730/* A subroutine of store_init_value. Splits non-constant static
731 initializer INIT into a constant part and generates code to
732 perform the non-constant part of the initialization to DEST.
733 Returns the code for the runtime init. */
734
735tree
736split_nonconstant_init (tree dest, tree init)
737{
738 tree code;
739
740 if (TREE_CODE (init) == TARGET_EXPR)
741 init = TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (init);
742 if (TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR)
743 {
744 init = cp_fully_fold (init);
745 code = push_stmt_list ();
746 if (split_nonconstant_init_1 (dest, init))
747 init = NULL_TREE;
748 code = pop_stmt_list (code);
749 DECL_INITIAL (dest) = init;
750 TREE_READONLY (dest) = 0;
751 }
752 else if (TREE_CODE (init) == STRING_CST
753 && array_of_runtime_bound_p (TREE_TYPE (dest)))
754 code = build_vec_init (dest, NULL_TREE, init, /*value-init*/false,
755 /*from array*/1, tf_warning_or_error);
756 else
757 code = build2 (INIT_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (dest), dest, init);
758
759 return code;
760}

762/* Perform appropriate conversions on the initial value of a variable,
763 store it in the declaration DECL,
764 and print any error messages that are appropriate.
765 If the init is invalid, store an ERROR_MARK.
766
767 C++: Note that INIT might be a TREE_LIST, which would mean that it is
768 a base class initializer for some aggregate type, hopefully compatible
769 with DECL. If INIT is a single element, and DECL is an aggregate
770 type, we silently convert INIT into a TREE_LIST, allowing a constructor
771 to be called.
772
773 If INIT is a TREE_LIST and there is no constructor, turn INIT
774 into a CONSTRUCTOR and use standard initialization techniques.
775 Perhaps a warning should be generated?
776
777 Returns code to be executed if initialization could not be performed
778 for static variable. In that case, caller must emit the code. */
779
780tree
781store_init_value (tree decl, tree init, vec<tree, va_gc>** cleanups, int flags)
782{
783 tree value, type;
784
785 /* If variable's type was invalidly declared, just ignore it. */
786
787 type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
788 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ERROR_MARK)
789 return NULL_TREE;
790
791 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
792 {
793 if (TREE_CODE (init) == TREE_LIST)
794 {
795 error ("constructor syntax used, but no constructor declared "
796 "for type %qT", type);
797 init = build_constructor_from_list (init_list_type_node, nreverse (init));
798 }
799 }
800
801 /* End of special C++ code. */
802
803 if (flags & LOOKUP_ALREADY_DIGESTED)
804 value = init;
805 else
806 /* Digest the specified initializer into an expression. */
807 value = digest_init_flags (type, init, flags, tf_warning_or_error);
808
809 value = extend_ref_init_temps (decl, value, cleanups);
810
811 /* In C++11 constant expression is a semantic, not syntactic, property.
812 In C++98, make sure that what we thought was a constant expression at
813 template definition time is still constant and otherwise perform this
814 as optimization, e.g. to fold SIZEOF_EXPRs in the initializer. */
815 if (decl_maybe_constant_var_p (decl) || TREE_STATIC (decl))
816 {
817 bool const_init;
818 value = instantiate_non_dependent_expr (value);
819 if (DECL_DECLARED_CONSTEXPR_P (decl)
820 || (DECL_IN_AGGR_P (decl)
821 && DECL_INITIALIZED_IN_CLASS_P (decl)
822 && !DECL_VAR_DECLARED_INLINE_P (decl)))
823 {
824 /* Diagnose a non-constant initializer for constexpr variable or
825 non-inline in-class-initialized static data member. */
826 if (processing_template_decl
827 && !require_potential_constant_expression (value))
828 value = error_mark_node;
829 else
830 value = cxx_constant_value (value, decl);
831 }
832 value = maybe_constant_init (value, decl);
833 if (TREE_CODE (value) == CONSTRUCTOR && cp_has_mutable_p (type))
834 /* Poison this CONSTRUCTOR so it can't be copied to another
835 constexpr variable. */
836 CONSTRUCTOR_MUTABLE_POISON (value) = true;
837 const_init = (reduced_constant_expression_p (value)
838 || error_operand_p (value));
839 DECL_INITIALIZED_BY_CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_P (decl) = const_init;
840 /* FIXME setting TREE_CONSTANT on refs breaks the back end. */
841 if (TREE_CODE (type) != REFERENCE_TYPE)
842 TREE_CONSTANT (decl) = const_init && decl_maybe_constant_var_p (decl);
843 }
844 value = cp_fully_fold (value);
845
846 /* Handle aggregate NSDMI in non-constant initializers, too. */
847 value = replace_placeholders (value, decl);
848
849 /* DECL may change value; purge caches. */
850 clear_cv_and_fold_caches ();
851
852 /* If the initializer is not a constant, fill in DECL_INITIAL with
853 the bits that are constant, and then return an expression that
854 will perform the dynamic initialization. */
855 if (value != error_mark_node
856 && (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (value)
857 || array_of_runtime_bound_p (type)
858 || ! reduced_constant_expression_p (value)))
859 return split_nonconstant_init (decl, value);
860 /* If the value is a constant, just put it in DECL_INITIAL. If DECL
861 is an automatic variable, the middle end will turn this into a
862 dynamic initialization later. */
863 DECL_INITIAL (decl) = value;
864 return NULL_TREE;
865}

867
868/* Give diagnostic about narrowing conversions within { }. */
869
870bool
871check_narrowing (tree type, tree init, tsubst_flags_t complain)
872{
873 tree ftype = unlowered_expr_type (init);
874 bool ok = true;
875 REAL_VALUE_TYPE d;
876
877 if (((!warn_narrowing || !(complain & tf_warning))
878 && cxx_dialect == cxx98)
879 || !ARITHMETIC_TYPE_P (type))
880 return ok;
881
882 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)
883 && TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
884 {
885 tree elttype = TREE_TYPE (type);
886 if (CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init) > 0)
887 ok &= check_narrowing (elttype, CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (init, 0)->value,
888 complain);
889 if (CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init) > 1)
890 ok &= check_narrowing (elttype, CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (init, 1)->value,
891 complain);
892 return ok;
893 }
894
895 init = fold_non_dependent_expr (init);
896
897 if (TREE_CODE (type) == INTEGER_TYPE
898 && TREE_CODE (ftype) == REAL_TYPE)
899 ok = false;
900 else if (INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (ftype)
901 && CP_INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (type))
902 {
903 if (TREE_CODE (ftype) == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
904 /* Check for narrowing based on the values of the enumeration. */
905 ftype = ENUM_UNDERLYING_TYPE (ftype);
906 if ((tree_int_cst_lt (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (type),
907 TYPE_MAX_VALUE (ftype))
908 || tree_int_cst_lt (TYPE_MIN_VALUE (ftype),
909 TYPE_MIN_VALUE (type)))
910 && (TREE_CODE (init) != INTEGER_CST
911 || !int_fits_type_p (init, type)))
912 ok = false;
913 }
914 else if (TREE_CODE (ftype) == REAL_TYPE
915 && TREE_CODE (type) == REAL_TYPE)
916 {
917 if (TYPE_PRECISION (type) < TYPE_PRECISION (ftype))
918 {
919 if (TREE_CODE (init) == REAL_CST)
920 {
921 /* Issue 703: Loss of precision is OK as long as the value is
922 within the representable range of the new type. */
923 REAL_VALUE_TYPE r;
924 d = TREE_REAL_CST (init);
925 real_convert (&r, TYPE_MODE (type), &d);
926 if (real_isinf (&r))
927 ok = false;
928 }
929 else
930 ok = false;
931 }
932 }
933 else if (INTEGRAL_OR_ENUMERATION_TYPE_P (ftype)
934 && TREE_CODE (type) == REAL_TYPE)
935 {
936 ok = false;
937 if (TREE_CODE (init) == INTEGER_CST)
938 {
939 d = real_value_from_int_cst (0, init);
940 if (exact_real_truncate (TYPE_MODE (type), &d))
941 ok = true;
942 }
943 }
944
945 bool almost_ok = ok;
946 if (!ok && !CONSTANT_CLASS_P (init) && (complain & tf_warning_or_error))
947 {
948 tree folded = cp_fully_fold (init);
949 if (TREE_CONSTANT (folded) && check_narrowing (type, folded, tf_none))
950 almost_ok = true;
951 }
952
953 if (!ok)
954 {
955 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (init, input_location);
956 if (cxx_dialect == cxx98)
957 {
958 if (complain & tf_warning)
959 warning_at (loc, OPT_Wnarrowing, "narrowing conversion of %qE "
960 "from %qT to %qT inside { } is ill-formed in C++11",
961 init, ftype, type);
962 ok = true;
963 }
964 else if (!CONSTANT_CLASS_P (init))
965 {
966 if (complain & tf_warning_or_error)
967 {
968 if ((!almost_ok || pedantic)
969 && pedwarn (loc, OPT_Wnarrowing,
970 "narrowing conversion of %qE "
971 "from %qT to %qT inside { }",
972 init, ftype, type)
973 && almost_ok)
974 inform (loc, " the expression has a constant value but is not "
975 "a C++ constant-expression");
976 ok = true;
977 }
978 }
979 else if (complain & tf_error)
980 {
981 int savederrorcount = errorcount;
982 global_dc->pedantic_errors = 1;
983 pedwarn (loc, OPT_Wnarrowing,
984 "narrowing conversion of %qE from %qT to %qT "
985 "inside { }", init, ftype, type);
986 if (errorcount == savederrorcount)
987 ok = true;
988 global_dc->pedantic_errors = flag_pedantic_errors;
989 }
990 }
991
992 return ok;
993}

995/* Process the initializer INIT for a variable of type TYPE, emitting
996 diagnostics for invalid initializers and converting the initializer as
997 appropriate.
998
999 For aggregate types, it assumes that reshape_init has already run, thus the
1000 initializer will have the right shape (brace elision has been undone).
1001
1002 NESTED is true iff we are being called for an element of a CONSTRUCTOR. */
1003
1004static tree
1005digest_init_r (tree type, tree init, bool nested, int flags,
1006 tsubst_flags_t complain)
1007{
1008 enum tree_code code = TREE_CODE (type);
1009
1010 if (error_operand_p (init))
1011 return error_mark_node;
1012
1013 gcc_assert (init);
1014
1015 /* We must strip the outermost array type when completing the type,
1016 because the its bounds might be incomplete at the moment. */
1017 if (!complete_type_or_maybe_complain (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
1018 ? TREE_TYPE (type) : type, NULL_TREE,
1019 complain))
1020 return error_mark_node;
1021
1022 /* Strip NON_LVALUE_EXPRs since we aren't using as an lvalue
1023 (g++.old-deja/g++.law/casts2.C). */
1024 if (TREE_CODE (init) == NON_LVALUE_EXPR)
1025 init = TREE_OPERAND (init, 0);
1026
1027 location_t loc = EXPR_LOC_OR_LOC (init, input_location);
1028
1029 /* Initialization of an array of chars from a string constant. The initializer
1030 can be optionally enclosed in braces, but reshape_init has already removed
1031 them if they were present. */
1032 if (code == ARRAY_TYPE)
1033 {
1034 if (nested && !TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
1035 {
1036 /* C++ flexible array members have a null domain. */
1037 pedwarn (loc, OPT_Wpedantic,
1038 "initialization of a flexible array member");
1039 }
1040
1041 tree typ1 = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (type));
1042 if (char_type_p (typ1)
1043 /*&& init */
1044 && TREE_CODE (init) == STRING_CST)
1045 {
1046 tree char_type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (init)));
1047
1048 if (TYPE_PRECISION (typ1) == BITS_PER_UNIT)
1049 {
1050 if (char_type != char_type_node)
1051 {
1052 if (complain & tf_error)
1053 error_at (loc, "char-array initialized from wide string");
1054 return error_mark_node;
1055 }
1056 }
1057 else
1058 {
1059 if (char_type == char_type_node)
1060 {
1061 if (complain & tf_error)
1062 error_at (loc,
1063 "int-array initialized from non-wide string");
1064 return error_mark_node;
1065 }
1066 else if (char_type != typ1)
1067 {
1068 if (complain & tf_error)
1069 error_at (loc, "int-array initialized from incompatible "
1070 "wide string");
1071 return error_mark_node;
1072 }
1073 }
1074
1075 if (type != TREE_TYPE (init)
1076 && !variably_modified_type_p (type, NULL_TREE))
1077 {
1078 init = copy_node (init);
1079 TREE_TYPE (init) = type;
1080 }
1081 if (TYPE_DOMAIN (type) && TREE_CONSTANT (TYPE_SIZE (type)))
1082 {
1083 /* Not a flexible array member. */
1084 int size = TREE_INT_CST_LOW (TYPE_SIZE (type));
1085 size = (size + BITS_PER_UNIT - 1) / BITS_PER_UNIT;
1086 /* In C it is ok to subtract 1 from the length of the string
1087 because it's ok to ignore the terminating null char that is
1088 counted in the length of the constant, but in C++ this would
1089 be invalid. */
1090 if (size < TREE_STRING_LENGTH (init))
1091 permerror (loc, "initializer-string for array "
1092 "of chars is too long");
1093 }
1094 return init;
1095 }
1096 }
1097
1098 /* Handle scalar types (including conversions) and references. */
1099 if ((TREE_CODE (type) != COMPLEX_TYPE
1100 || BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init))
1101 && (SCALAR_TYPE_P (type) || code == REFERENCE_TYPE))
1102 {
1103 if (nested)
1104 flags |= LOOKUP_NO_NARROWING;
1105 init = convert_for_initialization (0, type, init, flags,
1106 ICR_INIT, NULL_TREE, 0,
1107 complain);
1108
1109 return init;
1110 }
1111
1112 /* Come here only for aggregates: records, arrays, unions, complex numbers
1113 and vectors. */
1114 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
1115 || VECTOR_TYPE_P (type)
1116 || TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE
1117 || TREE_CODE (type) == UNION_TYPE
1118 || TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE);
1119
1120 /* "If T is a class type and the initializer list has a single
1121 element of type cv U, where U is T or a class derived from T,
1122 the object is initialized from that element." */
1123 if (flag_checking
1124 && cxx_dialect >= cxx11
1125 && BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)
1126 && CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init) == 1
1127 && ((CLASS_TYPE_P (type) && !CLASSTYPE_NON_AGGREGATE (type))
1128 || VECTOR_TYPE_P (type)))
1129 {
1130 tree elt = CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (init, 0)->value;
1131 if (reference_related_p (type, TREE_TYPE (elt)))
1132 /* We should have fixed this in reshape_init. */
1133 gcc_unreachable ();
1134 }
1135
1136 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)
1137 && !TYPE_NON_AGGREGATE_CLASS (type))
1138 return process_init_constructor (type, init, complain);
1139 else
1140 {
1141 if (COMPOUND_LITERAL_P (init) && TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
1142 {
1143 if (complain & tf_error)
1144 error_at (loc, "cannot initialize aggregate of type %qT with "
1145 "a compound literal", type);
1146
1147 return error_mark_node;
1148 }
1149
1150 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
1151 && !BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init))
1152 {
1153 /* Allow the result of build_array_copy and of
1154 build_value_init_noctor. */
1155 if ((TREE_CODE (init) == VEC_INIT_EXPR
1156 || TREE_CODE (init) == CONSTRUCTOR)
1157 && (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
1158 (type, TREE_TYPE (init))))
1159 return init;
1160
1161 if (complain & tf_error)
1162 error_at (loc, "array must be initialized with a brace-enclosed"
1163 " initializer");
1164 return error_mark_node;
1165 }
1166
1167 return convert_for_initialization (NULL_TREE, type, init,
1168 flags,
1169 ICR_INIT, NULL_TREE, 0,
1170 complain);
1171 }
1172}

1186/* Process the initializer INIT for an NSDMI DECL (a FIELD_DECL). */
1187tree
1188digest_nsdmi_init (tree decl, tree init)
1189{
1190 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (decl) == FIELD_DECL);
1191
1192 tree type = TREE_TYPE (decl);
1193 int flags = LOOKUP_IMPLICIT;
1194 if (DIRECT_LIST_INIT_P (init))
1195 flags = LOOKUP_NORMAL;
1196 if (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init)
1197 && CP_AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (type))

1206/* Set of flags used within process_init_constructor to describe the
1207 initializers. */
1208#define PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS 1
1209#define PICFLAG_NOT_ALL_CONSTANT 2
1210#define PICFLAG_NOT_ALL_SIMPLE 4
1211#define PICFLAG_SIDE_EFFECTS 8
1212
1213/* Given an initializer INIT, return the flag (PICFLAG_*) which better
1214 describe it. */
1215
1216static int
1217picflag_from_initializer (tree init)
1218{
1219 if (init == error_mark_node)
1220 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1221 else if (!TREE_CONSTANT (init))
1222 {
1223 if (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (init))
1224 return PICFLAG_SIDE_EFFECTS;
1225 else
1226 return PICFLAG_NOT_ALL_CONSTANT;
1227 }
1228 else if (!initializer_constant_valid_p (init, TREE_TYPE (init)))
1229 return PICFLAG_NOT_ALL_SIMPLE;
1230 return 0;
1231}

1233/* Adjust INIT for going into a CONSTRUCTOR. */
1234
1235static tree
1236massage_init_elt (tree type, tree init, tsubst_flags_t complain)
1237{
1238 init = digest_init_r (type, init, true, LOOKUP_IMPLICIT, complain);
1239 /* Strip a simple TARGET_EXPR when we know this is an initializer. */
1240 if (SIMPLE_TARGET_EXPR_P (init))
1241 init = TARGET_EXPR_INITIAL (init);
1242 /* When we defer constant folding within a statement, we may want to
1243 defer this folding as well. */
1244 tree t = fold_non_dependent_expr (init);
1245 t = maybe_constant_init (t);
1246 if (TREE_CONSTANT (t))
1247 init = t;
1248 return init;
1249}

1251/* Subroutine of process_init_constructor, which will process an initializer
1252 INIT for an array or vector of type TYPE. Returns the flags (PICFLAG_*)
1253 which describe the initializers. */
1254
1255static int
1256process_init_constructor_array (tree type, tree init,
1257 tsubst_flags_t complain)
1258{
1259 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT i, len = 0;
1260 int flags = 0;
1261 bool unbounded = false;
1262 constructor_elt *ce;
1263 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init);
1264
1265 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
1266 || VECTOR_TYPE_P (type));
1267
1268 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
1269 {
1270 /* C++ flexible array members have a null domain. */
1271 tree domain = TYPE_DOMAIN (type);
1272 if (domain && TREE_CONSTANT (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (domain)))
1273 len = wi::ext (wi::to_offset (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (domain))
1274 - wi::to_offset (TYPE_MIN_VALUE (domain)) + 1,
1275 TYPE_PRECISION (TREE_TYPE (domain)),
1276 TYPE_SIGN (TREE_TYPE (domain))).to_uhwi ();
1277 else
1278 unbounded = true; /* Take as many as there are. */
1279 }
1280 else
1281 /* Vectors are like simple fixed-size arrays. */
1282 len = TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (type);
1283
1284 /* There must not be more initializers than needed. */
1285 if (!unbounded && vec_safe_length (v) > len)
1286 {
1287 if (complain & tf_error)
1288 error ("too many initializers for %qT", type);
1289 else
1290 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1291 }
1292
1293 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (v, i, ce)
1294 {
1295 if (ce->index)
1296 {
1297 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (ce->index) == INTEGER_CST);
1298 if (compare_tree_int (ce->index, i) != 0)
1299 {
1300 ce->value = error_mark_node;
1301 sorry ("non-trivial designated initializers not supported");
1302 }
1303 }
1304 else
1305 ce->index = size_int (i);
1306 gcc_assert (ce->value);
1307 ce->value = massage_init_elt (TREE_TYPE (type), ce->value, complain);
1308
1309 if (ce->value != error_mark_node)
1310 gcc_assert (same_type_ignoring_top_level_qualifiers_p
1311 (TREE_TYPE (type), TREE_TYPE (ce->value)));
1312
1313 flags |= picflag_from_initializer (ce->value);
1314 }
1315
1316 /* No more initializers. If the array is unbounded, we are done. Otherwise,
1317 we must add initializers ourselves. */
1318 if (!unbounded)
1319 for (; i < len; ++i)
1320 {
1321 tree next;
1322
1323 if (type_build_ctor_call (TREE_TYPE (type)))
1324 {
1325 /* If this type needs constructors run for default-initialization,
1326 we can't rely on the back end to do it for us, so make the
1327 initialization explicit by list-initializing from T{}. */
1328 next = build_constructor (init_list_type_node, NULL);
1329 next = massage_init_elt (TREE_TYPE (type), next, complain);
1330 if (initializer_zerop (next))
1331 /* The default zero-initialization is fine for us; don't
1332 add anything to the CONSTRUCTOR. */
1333 next = NULL_TREE;
1334 }
1335 else if (!zero_init_p (TREE_TYPE (type)))
1336 next = build_zero_init (TREE_TYPE (type),
1337 /*nelts=*/NULL_TREE,
1338 /*static_storage_p=*/false);
1339 else
1340 /* The default zero-initialization is fine for us; don't
1341 add anything to the CONSTRUCTOR. */
1342 next = NULL_TREE;
1343
1344 if (next)
1345 {
1346 flags |= picflag_from_initializer (next);
1347 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (v, size_int (i), next);
1348 }
1349 }
1350
1351 CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init) = v;
1352 return flags;
1353}
1354
1355/* Subroutine of process_init_constructor, which will process an initializer
1356 INIT for a class of type TYPE. Returns the flags (PICFLAG_*) which describe
1357 the initializers. */
1358
1359static int
1360process_init_constructor_record (tree type, tree init,
1361 tsubst_flags_t complain)
1362{
1363 vec<constructor_elt, va_gc> *v = NULL;
1364 tree field;
1365 int skipped = 0;
1366
1367 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE);
1368 gcc_assert (!CLASSTYPE_VBASECLASSES (type));
1369 gcc_assert (!TYPE_BINFO (type)
1370 || cxx_dialect >= cxx1z
1371 || !BINFO_N_BASE_BINFOS (TYPE_BINFO (type)));
1372 gcc_assert (!TYPE_POLYMORPHIC_P (type));
1373
1374 restart:
1375 int flags = 0;
1376 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT idx = 0;
1377 /* Generally, we will always have an index for each initializer (which is
1378 a FIELD_DECL, put by reshape_init), but compound literals don't go trough
1379 reshape_init. So we need to handle both cases. */
1380 for (field = TYPE_FIELDS (type); field; field = DECL_CHAIN (field))
1381 {
1382 tree next;
1383 tree type;
1384
1385 if (!DECL_NAME (field) && DECL_C_BIT_FIELD (field))
1386 continue;
1387
1388 if (TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL
1389 || (DECL_ARTIFICIAL (field)
1390 && !(cxx_dialect >= cxx1z && DECL_FIELD_IS_BASE (field))))
1391 continue;
1392
1393 /* If this is a bitfield, first convert to the declared type. */
1394 type = TREE_TYPE (field);
1395 if (DECL_BIT_FIELD_TYPE (field))
1396 type = DECL_BIT_FIELD_TYPE (field);
1397 if (type == error_mark_node)
1398 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1399
1400 if (idx < CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init))
1401 {
1402 constructor_elt *ce = &(*CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init))[idx];
1403 if (ce->index)
1404 {
1405 /* We can have either a FIELD_DECL or an IDENTIFIER_NODE. The
1406 latter case can happen in templates where lookup has to be
1407 deferred. */
1408 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (ce->index) == FIELD_DECL
1409 || identifier_p (ce->index));
1410 if (ce->index != field
1411 && ce->index != DECL_NAME (field))
1412 {
1413 ce->value = error_mark_node;
1414 sorry ("non-trivial designated initializers not supported");
1415 }
1416 }
1417
1418 gcc_assert (ce->value);
1419 next = massage_init_elt (type, ce->value, complain);
1420 ++idx;
1421 }
1422 else if (DECL_INITIAL (field))
1423 {
1424 if (skipped > 0)
1425 {
1426 /* We're using an NSDMI past a field with implicit
1427 zero-init. Go back and make it explicit. */
1428 skipped = -1;
1429 vec_safe_truncate (v, 0);
1430 goto restart;
1431 }
1432 /* C++14 aggregate NSDMI. */
1433 next = get_nsdmi (field, /*ctor*/false);
1434 }
1435 else if (type_build_ctor_call (TREE_TYPE (field)))
1436 {
1437 /* If this type needs constructors run for
1438 default-initialization, we can't rely on the back end to do it
1439 for us, so build up TARGET_EXPRs. If the type in question is
1440 a class, just build one up; if it's an array, recurse. */
1441 next = build_constructor (init_list_type_node, NULL);
1442 next = massage_init_elt (TREE_TYPE (field), next, complain);
1443
1444 /* Warn when some struct elements are implicitly initialized. */
1445 if ((complain & tf_warning)
1446 && !EMPTY_CONSTRUCTOR_P (init))
1447 warning (OPT_Wmissing_field_initializers,
1448 "missing initializer for member %qD", field);
1449 }
1450 else
1451 {
1452 const_tree fldtype = TREE_TYPE (field);
1453 if (TREE_CODE (fldtype) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
1454 {
1455 if (complain & tf_error)
1456 error ("member %qD is uninitialized reference", field);
1457 else
1458 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1459 }
1460 else if (CLASSTYPE_REF_FIELDS_NEED_INIT (fldtype))
1461 {
1462 if (complain & tf_error)
1463 error ("member %qD with uninitialized reference fields", field);
1464 else
1465 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1466 }
1467
1468 /* Warn when some struct elements are implicitly initialized
1469 to zero. However, avoid issuing the warning for flexible
1470 array members since they need not have any elements. */
1471 if ((TREE_CODE (fldtype) != ARRAY_TYPE || TYPE_DOMAIN (fldtype))
1472 && (complain & tf_warning)
1473 && !EMPTY_CONSTRUCTOR_P (init))
1474 warning (OPT_Wmissing_field_initializers,
1475 "missing initializer for member %qD", field);
1476
1477 if (!zero_init_p (fldtype)
1478 || skipped < 0)
1479 next = build_zero_init (TREE_TYPE (field), /*nelts=*/NULL_TREE,
1480 /*static_storage_p=*/false);
1481 else
1482 {
1483 /* The default zero-initialization is fine for us; don't
1484 add anything to the CONSTRUCTOR. */
1485 skipped = 1;
1486 continue;
1487 }
1488 }
1489
1490 /* If this is a bitfield, now convert to the lowered type. */
1491 if (type != TREE_TYPE (field))
1492 next = cp_convert_and_check (TREE_TYPE (field), next, complain);
1493 flags |= picflag_from_initializer (next);
1494 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (v, field, next);
1495 }
1496
1497 if (idx < CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS (init))
1498 {
1499 if (complain & tf_error)
1500 error ("too many initializers for %qT", type);
1501 else
1502 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1503 }
1504
1505 CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init) = v;
1506 return flags;
1507}

1509/* Subroutine of process_init_constructor, which will process a single
1510 initializer INIT for a union of type TYPE. Returns the flags (PICFLAG_*)
1511 which describe the initializer. */
1512
1513static int
1514process_init_constructor_union (tree type, tree init,
1515 tsubst_flags_t complain)
1516{
1517 constructor_elt *ce;
1518 int len;
1519
1520 /* If the initializer was empty, use the union's NSDMI if it has one.
1521 Otherwise use default zero initialization. */
1522 if (vec_safe_is_empty (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init)))
1523 {
1524 for (tree field = TYPE_FIELDS (type); field; field = TREE_CHAIN (field))
1525 {
1526 if (TREE_CODE (field) == FIELD_DECL
1527 && DECL_INITIAL (field) != NULL_TREE)
1528 {
1529 CONSTRUCTOR_APPEND_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init),
1530 field,
1531 get_nsdmi (field, /*in_ctor=*/false));
1532 break;
1533 }
1534 }
1535
1536 if (vec_safe_is_empty (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init)))
1537 return 0;
1538 }
1539
1540 len = CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init)->length ();
1541 if (len > 1)
1542 {
1543 if (!(complain & tf_error))
1544 return PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS;
1545 error ("too many initializers for %qT", type);
1546 CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init)->block_remove (1, len-1);
1547 }
1548
1549 ce = &(*CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (init))[0];
1550
1551 /* If this element specifies a field, initialize via that field. */
1552 if (ce->index)
1553 {
1554 if (TREE_CODE (ce->index) == FIELD_DECL)
1555 ;
1556 else if (identifier_p (ce->index))
1557 {
1558 /* This can happen within a cast, see g++.dg/opt/cse2.C. */
1559 tree name = ce->index;
1560 tree field;
1561 for (field = TYPE_FIELDS (type); field; field = TREE_CHAIN (field))
1562 if (DECL_NAME (field) == name)
1563 break;
1564 if (!field)
1565 {
1566 if (complain & tf_error)
1567 error ("no field %qD found in union being initialized",
1568 field);
1569 ce->value = error_mark_node;
1570 }
1571 ce->index = field;
1572 }
1573 else
1574 {
1575 gcc_assert (TREE_CODE (ce->index) == INTEGER_CST
1576 || TREE_CODE (ce->index) == RANGE_EXPR);
1577 if (complain & tf_error)
1578 error ("index value instead of field name in union initializer");
1579 ce->value = error_mark_node;
1580 }
1581 }
1582 else
1583 {
1584 /* Find the first named field. ANSI decided in September 1990
1585 that only named fields count here. */
1586 tree field = TYPE_FIELDS (type);
1587 while (field && (!DECL_NAME (field) || TREE_CODE (field) != FIELD_DECL))
1588 field = TREE_CHAIN (field);
1589 if (field == NULL_TREE)
1590 {
1591 if (complain & tf_error)
1592 error ("too many initializers for %qT", type);
1593 ce->value = error_mark_node;
1594 }
1595 ce->index = field;
1596 }
1597
1598 if (ce->value && ce->value != error_mark_node)
1599 ce->value = massage_init_elt (TREE_TYPE (ce->index), ce->value, complain);
1600
1601 return picflag_from_initializer (ce->value);
1602}

1604/* Process INIT, a constructor for a variable of aggregate type TYPE. The
1605 constructor is a brace-enclosed initializer, and will be modified in-place.
1606
1607 Each element is converted to the right type through digest_init, and
1608 missing initializers are added following the language rules (zero-padding,
1609 etc.).
1610
1611 After the execution, the initializer will have TREE_CONSTANT if all elts are
1612 constant, and TREE_STATIC set if, in addition, all elts are simple enough
1613 constants that the assembler and linker can compute them.
1614
1615 The function returns the initializer itself, or error_mark_node in case
1616 of error. */
1617
1618static tree
1619process_init_constructor (tree type, tree init, tsubst_flags_t complain)
1620{
1621 int flags;
1622
1623 gcc_assert (BRACE_ENCLOSED_INITIALIZER_P (init));
1624
1625 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE || VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
1626 flags = process_init_constructor_array (type, init, complain);
1627 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == RECORD_TYPE)
1628 flags = process_init_constructor_record (type, init, complain);
1629 else if (TREE_CODE (type) == UNION_TYPE)
1630 flags = process_init_constructor_union (type, init, complain);
1631 else
1632 gcc_unreachable ();
1633
1634 if (flags & PICFLAG_ERRONEOUS)
1635 return error_mark_node;
1636
1637 TREE_TYPE (init) = type;
1638 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE && TYPE_DOMAIN (type) == NULL_TREE)
1639 cp_complete_array_type (&TREE_TYPE (init), init, /*do_default=*/0);
1640 if (flags & PICFLAG_SIDE_EFFECTS)
1641 {
1642 TREE_CONSTANT (init) = false;
1643 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (init) = true;
1644 }
1645 else if (flags & PICFLAG_NOT_ALL_CONSTANT)
1646 /* Make sure TREE_CONSTANT isn't set from build_constructor. */
1647 TREE_CONSTANT (init) = false;
1648 else
1649 {
1650 TREE_CONSTANT (init) = 1;
1651 if (!(flags & PICFLAG_NOT_ALL_SIMPLE))
1652 TREE_STATIC (init) = 1;
1653 }
1654 return init;
1655}

1657/* Given a structure or union value DATUM, construct and return
1658 the structure or union component which results from narrowing
1659 that value to the base specified in BASETYPE. For example, given the
1660 hierarchy
1661
1662 class L { int ii; };
1663 class A : L { ... };
1664 class B : L { ... };
1665 class C : A, B { ... };
1666
1667 and the declaration
1668
1669 C x;
1670
1671 then the expression
1672
1673 x.A::ii refers to the ii member of the L part of
1674 the A part of the C object named by X. In this case,
1675 DATUM would be x, and BASETYPE would be A.
1676
1677 I used to think that this was nonconformant, that the standard specified
1678 that first we look up ii in A, then convert x to an L& and pull out the
1679 ii part. But in fact, it does say that we convert x to an A&; A here
1680 is known as the "naming class". (jason 2000-12-19)
1681
1682 BINFO_P points to a variable initialized either to NULL_TREE or to the
1683 binfo for the specific base subobject we want to convert to. */
1684
1685tree
1686build_scoped_ref (tree datum, tree basetype, tree* binfo_p)
1687{
1688 tree binfo;
1689
1690 if (datum == error_mark_node)
1691 return error_mark_node;
1692 if (*binfo_p)
1693 binfo = *binfo_p;
1694 else
1695 binfo = lookup_base (TREE_TYPE (datum), basetype, ba_check,
1696 NULL, tf_warning_or_error);
1697
1698 if (!binfo || binfo == error_mark_node)
1699 {
1700 *binfo_p = NULL_TREE;
1701 if (!binfo)
1702 error_not_base_type (basetype, TREE_TYPE (datum));
1703 return error_mark_node;
1704 }
1705
1706 *binfo_p = binfo;
1707 return build_base_path (PLUS_EXPR, datum, binfo, 1,
1708 tf_warning_or_error);
1709}

1711/* Build a reference to an object specified by the C++ `->' operator.
1712 Usually this just involves dereferencing the object, but if the
1713 `->' operator is overloaded, then such overloads must be
1714 performed until an object which does not have the `->' operator
1715 overloaded is found. An error is reported when circular pointer
1716 delegation is detected. */
1717
1718tree
1719build_x_arrow (location_t loc, tree expr, tsubst_flags_t complain)
1720{
1721 tree orig_expr = expr;
1722 tree type = TREE_TYPE (expr);
1723 tree last_rval = NULL_TREE;
1724 vec<tree, va_gc> *types_memoized = NULL;
1725
1726 if (type == error_mark_node)
1727 return error_mark_node;
1728
1729 if (processing_template_decl)
1730 {
1731 if (type && TREE_CODE (type) == POINTER_TYPE
1732 && !dependent_scope_p (TREE_TYPE (type)))
1733 /* Pointer to current instantiation, don't treat as dependent. */;
1734 else if (type_dependent_expression_p (expr))
1735 return build_min_nt_loc (loc, ARROW_EXPR, expr);
1736 expr = build_non_dependent_expr (expr);
1737 }
1738
1739 if (MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
1740 {
1741 struct tinst_level *actual_inst = current_instantiation ();
1742 tree fn = NULL;
1743
1744 while ((expr = build_new_op (loc, COMPONENT_REF,
1745 LOOKUP_NORMAL, expr, NULL_TREE, NULL_TREE,
1746 &fn, complain)))
1747 {
1748 if (expr == error_mark_node)
1749 return error_mark_node;
1750
1751 /* This provides a better instantiation backtrace in case of
1752 error. */
1753 if (fn && DECL_USE_TEMPLATE (fn))
1754 push_tinst_level_loc (fn,
1755 (current_instantiation () != actual_inst)
1756 ? DECL_SOURCE_LOCATION (fn)
1757 : input_location);
1758 fn = NULL;
1759
1760 if (vec_member (TREE_TYPE (expr), types_memoized))
1761 {
1762 if (complain & tf_error)
1763 error ("circular pointer delegation detected");
1764 return error_mark_node;
1765 }
1766
1767 vec_safe_push (types_memoized, TREE_TYPE (expr));
1768 last_rval = expr;
1769 }
1770
1771 while (current_instantiation () != actual_inst)
1772 pop_tinst_level ();
1773
1774 if (last_rval == NULL_TREE)
1775 {
1776 if (complain & tf_error)
1777 error ("base operand of %<->%> has non-pointer type %qT", type);
1778 return error_mark_node;
1779 }
1780
1781 if (TREE_CODE (TREE_TYPE (last_rval)) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
1782 last_rval = convert_from_reference (last_rval);
1783 }
1784 else
1785 last_rval = decay_conversion (expr, complain);
1786
1787 if (TYPE_PTR_P (TREE_TYPE (last_rval)))
1788 {
1789 if (processing_template_decl)
1790 {
1791 expr = build_min (ARROW_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (TREE_TYPE (last_rval)),
1792 orig_expr);
1793 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (expr) = TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (last_rval);
1794 return expr;
1795 }
1796
1797 return cp_build_indirect_ref (last_rval, RO_NULL, complain);
1798 }
1799
1800 if (complain & tf_error)
1801 {
1802 if (types_memoized)
1803 error ("result of %<operator->()%> yields non-pointer result");
1804 else
1805 error ("base operand of %<->%> is not a pointer");
1806 }
1807 return error_mark_node;
1808}

1810/* Return an expression for "DATUM .* COMPONENT". DATUM has not
1811 already been checked out to be of aggregate type. */
1812
1813tree
1814build_m_component_ref (tree datum, tree component, tsubst_flags_t complain)
1815{
1816 tree ptrmem_type;
1817 tree objtype;
1818 tree type;
1819 tree binfo;
1820 tree ctype;
1821
1822 if (error_operand_p (datum) || error_operand_p (component))
1823 return error_mark_node;
1824
1825 datum = mark_lvalue_use (datum);
1826 component = mark_rvalue_use (component);
1827
1828 ptrmem_type = TREE_TYPE (component);
1829 if (!TYPE_PTRMEM_P (ptrmem_type))
1830 {
1831 if (complain & tf_error)
1832 error ("%qE cannot be used as a member pointer, since it is of "
1833 "type %qT", component, ptrmem_type);
1834 return error_mark_node;
1835 }
1836
1837 objtype = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (TREE_TYPE (datum));
1838 if (! MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (objtype))
1839 {
1840 if (complain & tf_error)
1841 error ("cannot apply member pointer %qE to %qE, which is of "
1842 "non-class type %qT", component, datum, objtype);
1843 return error_mark_node;
1844 }
1845
1846 type = TYPE_PTRMEM_POINTED_TO_TYPE (ptrmem_type);
1847 ctype = complete_type (TYPE_PTRMEM_CLASS_TYPE (ptrmem_type));
1848
1849 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (ctype))
1850 {
1851 if (!same_type_p (ctype, objtype))
1852 goto mismatch;
1853 binfo = NULL;
1854 }
1855 else
1856 {
1857 binfo = lookup_base (objtype, ctype, ba_check, NULL, complain);
1858
1859 if (!binfo)
1860 {
1861 mismatch:
1862 if (complain & tf_error)
1863 error ("pointer to member type %qT incompatible with object "
1864 "type %qT", type, objtype);
1865 return error_mark_node;
1866 }
1867 else if (binfo == error_mark_node)
1868 return error_mark_node;
1869 }
1870
1871 if (TYPE_PTRDATAMEM_P (ptrmem_type))
1872 {
1873 cp_lvalue_kind kind = lvalue_kind (datum);
1874 tree ptype;
1875
1876 /* Compute the type of the field, as described in [expr.ref].
1877 There's no such thing as a mutable pointer-to-member, so
1878 things are not as complex as they are for references to
1879 non-static data members. */
1880 type = cp_build_qualified_type (type,
1881 (cp_type_quals (type)
1882 | cp_type_quals (TREE_TYPE (datum))));
1883
1884 datum = build_address (datum);
1885
1886 /* Convert object to the correct base. */
1887 if (binfo)
1888 {
1889 datum = build_base_path (PLUS_EXPR, datum, binfo, 1, complain);
1890 if (datum == error_mark_node)
1891 return error_mark_node;
1892 }
1893
1894 /* Build an expression for "object + offset" where offset is the
1895 value stored in the pointer-to-data-member. */
1896 ptype = build_pointer_type (type);
1897 datum = fold_build_pointer_plus (fold_convert (ptype, datum), component);
1898 datum = cp_build_indirect_ref (datum, RO_NULL, complain);
1899 if (datum == error_mark_node)
1900 return error_mark_node;
1901
1902 /* If the object expression was an rvalue, return an rvalue. */
1903 if (kind & clk_class)
1904 datum = rvalue (datum);
1905 else if (kind & clk_rvalueref)
1906 datum = move (datum);
1907 return datum;
1908 }
1909 else
1910 {
1911 /* 5.5/6: In a .* expression whose object expression is an rvalue, the
1912 program is ill-formed if the second operand is a pointer to member
1913 function with ref-qualifier &. In a .* expression whose object
1914 expression is an lvalue, the program is ill-formed if the second
1915 operand is a pointer to member function with ref-qualifier &&. */
1916 if (FUNCTION_REF_QUALIFIED (type))
1917 {
1918 bool lval = lvalue_p (datum);
1919 if (lval && FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED (type))
1920 {
1921 if (complain & tf_error)
1922 error ("pointer-to-member-function type %qT requires an rvalue",
1923 ptrmem_type);
1924 return error_mark_node;
1925 }
1926 else if (!lval && !FUNCTION_RVALUE_QUALIFIED (type))
1927 {
1928 if (complain & tf_error)
1929 error ("pointer-to-member-function type %qT requires an lvalue",
1930 ptrmem_type);
1931 return error_mark_node;
1932 }
1933 }
1934 return build2 (OFFSET_REF, type, datum, component);
1935 }
1936}

1938/* Return a tree node for the expression TYPENAME '(' PARMS ')'. */
1939
1940tree
1941build_functional_cast (tree exp, tree parms, tsubst_flags_t complain)
1942{
1943 /* This is either a call to a constructor,
1944 or a C cast in C++'s `functional' notation. */
1945
1946 /* The type to which we are casting. */
1947 tree type;
1948 vec<tree, va_gc> *parmvec;
1949
1950 if (error_operand_p (exp) || parms == error_mark_node)
1951 return error_mark_node;
1952
1953 if (TREE_CODE (exp) == TYPE_DECL)
1954 {
1955 type = TREE_TYPE (exp);
1956
1957 if (complain & tf_warning
1958 && TREE_DEPRECATED (type)
1959 && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (exp))
1960 cp_warn_deprecated_use (type);
1961 }
1962 else
1963 type = exp;
1964
1965 /* We need to check this explicitly, since value-initialization of
1966 arrays is allowed in other situations. */
1967 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE)
1968 {
1969 if (complain & tf_error)
1970 error ("functional cast to array type %qT", type);
1971 return error_mark_node;
1972 }
1973
1974 if (tree anode = type_uses_auto (type))
1975 {
1976 if (!CLASS_PLACEHOLDER_TEMPLATE (anode))
1977 {
1978 if (complain & tf_error)
1979 error ("invalid use of %qT", anode);
1980 return error_mark_node;
1981 }
1982 else if (!parms)
1983 {
1984 if (complain & tf_error)
1985 error ("cannot deduce template arguments for %qT from ()", anode);
1986 return error_mark_node;
1987 }
1988 else
1989 type = do_auto_deduction (type, parms, anode, complain,
1990 adc_variable_type);
1991 }
1992
1993 if (processing_template_decl)
1994 {
1995 tree t;
1996
1997 /* Diagnose this even in a template. We could also try harder
1998 to give all the usual errors when the type and args are
1999 non-dependent... */
2000 if (TREE_CODE (type) == REFERENCE_TYPE && !parms)
2001 {
2002 if (complain & tf_error)
2003 error ("invalid value-initialization of reference type");
2004 return error_mark_node;
2005 }
2006
2007 t = build_min (CAST_EXPR, type, parms);
2008 /* We don't know if it will or will not have side effects. */
2009 TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS (t) = 1;
2010 return t;
2011 }
2012
2013 if (! MAYBE_CLASS_TYPE_P (type))
2014 {
2015 if (parms == NULL_TREE)
2016 {
2017 if (VOID_TYPE_P (type))
2018 return void_node;
2019 return build_value_init (cv_unqualified (type), complain);
2020 }
2021
2022 /* This must build a C cast. */
2023 parms = build_x_compound_expr_from_list (parms, ELK_FUNC_CAST, complain);
2024 return cp_build_c_cast (type, parms, complain);
2025 }
2026
2027 /* Prepare to evaluate as a call to a constructor. If this expression
2028 is actually used, for example,
2029
2030 return X (arg1, arg2, ...);
2031
2032 then the slot being initialized will be filled in. */
2033
2034 if (!complete_type_or_maybe_complain (type, NULL_TREE, complain))
2035 return error_mark_node;
2036 if (abstract_virtuals_error_sfinae (ACU_CAST, type, complain))
2037 return error_mark_node;
2038
2039 /* [expr.type.conv]
2040
2041 If the expression list is a single-expression, the type
2042 conversion is equivalent (in definedness, and if defined in
2043 meaning) to the corresponding cast expression. */
2044 if (parms && TREE_CHAIN (parms) == NULL_TREE)
2045 return cp_build_c_cast (type, TREE_VALUE (parms), complain);
2046
2047 /* [expr.type.conv]
2048
2049 The expression T(), where T is a simple-type-specifier for a
2050 non-array complete object type or the (possibly cv-qualified)
2051 void type, creates an rvalue of the specified type, which is
2052 value-initialized. */
2053
2054 if (parms == NULL_TREE)
2055 {
2056 exp = build_value_init (type, complain);
2057 exp = get_target_expr_sfinae (exp, complain);
2058 return exp;
2059 }
2060
2061 /* Call the constructor. */
2062 parmvec = make_tree_vector ();
2063 for (; parms != NULL_TREE; parms = TREE_CHAIN (parms))
2064 vec_safe_push (parmvec, TREE_VALUE (parms));
2065 exp = build_special_member_call (NULL_TREE, complete_ctor_identifier,
2066 &parmvec, type, LOOKUP_NORMAL, complain);
2067 release_tree_vector (parmvec);
2068
2069 if (exp == error_mark_node)
2070 return error_mark_node;
2071
2072 return build_cplus_new (type, exp, complain);
2073}

2076/* Add new exception specifier SPEC, to the LIST we currently have.
2077 If it's already in LIST then do nothing.
2078 Moan if it's bad and we're allowed to. COMPLAIN < 0 means we
2079 know what we're doing. */
2080
2081tree
2082add_exception_specifier (tree list, tree spec, int complain)
2083{
2084 bool ok;
2085 tree core = spec;
2086 bool is_ptr;
2087 diagnostic_t diag_type = DK_UNSPECIFIED; /* none */
2088
2089 if (spec == error_mark_node)
2090 return list;
2091
2092 gcc_assert (spec && (!list || TREE_VALUE (list)));
2093
2094 /* [except.spec] 1, type in an exception specifier shall not be
2095 incomplete, or pointer or ref to incomplete other than pointer
2096 to cv void. */
2097 is_ptr = TYPE_PTR_P (core);
2098 if (is_ptr || TREE_CODE (core) == REFERENCE_TYPE)
2099 core = TREE_TYPE (core);
2100 if (complain < 0)
2101 ok = true;
2102 else if (VOID_TYPE_P (core))
2103 ok = is_ptr;
2104 else if (TREE_CODE (core) == TEMPLATE_TYPE_PARM)
2105 ok = true;
2106 else if (processing_template_decl)
2107 ok = true;
2108 else
2109 {
2110 ok = true;
2111 /* 15.4/1 says that types in an exception specifier must be complete,
2112 but it seems more reasonable to only require this on definitions
2113 and calls. So just give a pedwarn at this point; we will give an
2114 error later if we hit one of those two cases. */
2115 if (!COMPLETE_TYPE_P (complete_type (core)))
2116 diag_type = DK_PEDWARN; /* pedwarn */
2117 }
2118
2119 if (ok)
2120 {
2121 tree probe;
2122
2123 for (probe = list; probe; probe = TREE_CHAIN (probe))
2124 if (same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (probe), spec))
2125 break;
2126 if (!probe)
2127 list = tree_cons (NULL_TREE, spec, list);
2128 }
2129 else
2130 diag_type = DK_ERROR; /* error */
2131
2132 if (diag_type != DK_UNSPECIFIED
2133 && (complain & tf_warning_or_error))
2134 cxx_incomplete_type_diagnostic (NULL_TREE, core, diag_type);
2135
2136 return list;
2137}

2142nothrow_spec_p_uninst (const_tree spec)
2143{
2144 if (DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P (spec))
2145 return false;

2149/* Combine the two exceptions specifier lists LIST and ADD, and return
2150 their union. */
2151
2152tree
2153merge_exception_specifiers (tree list, tree add)
2154{
2155 tree noex, orig_list;
2156
2157 /* No exception-specifier or noexcept(false) are less strict than
2158 anything else. Prefer the newer variant (LIST). */
2159 if (!list || list == noexcept_false_spec)
2160 return list;
2161 else if (!add || add == noexcept_false_spec)
2162 return add;
2163
2164 /* noexcept(true) and throw() are stricter than anything else.
2165 As above, prefer the more recent one (LIST). */
2166 if (nothrow_spec_p_uninst (add))
2167 return list;
2168
2169 /* Two implicit noexcept specs (e.g. on a destructor) are equivalent. */
2170 if (UNEVALUATED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P (add)
2171 && UNEVALUATED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P (list))
2172 return list;
2173 /* We should have instantiated other deferred noexcept specs by now. */
2174 gcc_assert (!DEFERRED_NOEXCEPT_SPEC_P (add));
2175
2176 if (nothrow_spec_p_uninst (list))
2177 return add;
2178 noex = TREE_PURPOSE (list);
2179 gcc_checking_assert (!TREE_PURPOSE (add)
2180 || errorcount || !flag_exceptions
2181 || cp_tree_equal (noex, TREE_PURPOSE (add)));
2182
2183 /* Combine the dynamic-exception-specifiers, if any. */
2184 orig_list = list;
2185 for (; add && TREE_VALUE (add); add = TREE_CHAIN (add))
2186 {
2187 tree spec = TREE_VALUE (add);
2188 tree probe;
2189
2190 for (probe = orig_list; probe && TREE_VALUE (probe);
2191 probe = TREE_CHAIN (probe))
2192 if (same_type_p (TREE_VALUE (probe), spec))
2193 break;
2194 if (!probe)
2195 {
2196 spec = build_tree_list (NULL_TREE, spec);
2197 TREE_CHAIN (spec) = list;
2198 list = spec;
2199 }
2200 }
2201
2202 /* Keep the noexcept-specifier at the beginning of the list. */
2203 if (noex != TREE_PURPOSE (list))
2204 list = tree_cons (noex, TREE_VALUE (list), TREE_CHAIN (list));
2205
2206 return list;
2207}

2209/* Subroutine of build_call. Ensure that each of the types in the
2210 exception specification is complete. Technically, 15.4/1 says that
2211 they need to be complete when we see a declaration of the function,
2212 but we should be able to get away with only requiring this when the
2213 function is defined or called. See also add_exception_specifier. */
2214
2215void
2216require_complete_eh_spec_types (tree fntype, tree decl)
2217{
2218 tree raises;
2219 /* Don't complain about calls to op new. */
2220 if (decl && DECL_ARTIFICIAL (decl))
2221 return;
2222 for (raises = TYPE_RAISES_EXCEPTIONS (fntype); raises;
2223 raises = TREE_CHAIN (raises))
2224 {
2225 tree type = TREE_VALUE (raises);
2226 if (type && !COMPLETE_TYPE_P (type))
2227 {
2228 if (decl)
2229 error
2230 ("call to function %qD which throws incomplete type %q#T",
2231 decl, type);
2232 else
2233 error ("call to function which throws incomplete type %q#T",
2234 decl);
2235 }
2236 }
2237}
